description: WNV transmitted between birds by ornithophilic mosquitoes and is occasionally transmitted to other animals such as reptiles and mammal. Most people infected with WNV either don't develop signs or symptoms or have only minor ones, such as a mild flu-like fevers and mild headache. Mild signs and symptoms of a WNV infection generally go away on their own.
name: West Nile Virus (WNV) Antibodies and Antigens
